  "reasoning": "I am at the Shop Phase with $4, two solid jokers (Crafty Joker and Acrobat) that already provide a strong scoring engine. The available shop options are limited: Odd Todd for $4 offers only marginal chip gains, Neptune for $3 levels up a Straight Flush (a hand type we have no synergy for), and a Jumbo Standard Pack for $6 which we cannot afford without selling a joker. Selling either joker would significantly weaken our immediate ability to beat the upcoming Boss Blind. With our current setup—a flush scores about 620 points normally and about 1860 on the final hand thanks to Acrobat—we can comfortably defeat any Ante‑1 Boss Blind, earn the blind reward, and have leftover hands for extra money. Spending all $4 now on Odd Todd would leave us broke and only slightly improve a strategy that is already sufficient, while saving the money gives us $4 going into the next shop where we may find a more impactful joker or the Wasteful voucher. Therefore the optimal decision is to skip the shop and advance to the Boss Blind."
